OL,3,CCommissioner denies blocking scrutiny
OL,4,Cover day centre closures
OL,6,F"Birmingham Local Conservatives are
OL,7,Freally disappointed in this decision
OL,8,Fto not allow the Day Centres decision
OL,9,Fto be called in as they feel it's a
OL,10,Fmistake and needs more scrutiny to
OL,11,Fprotect the council from the risk of
OL,12,Fincreased costs and legal challenge,
OL,13,Fas well as protecting vulnerable
OL,14,Fservice users".
OL,16,FPreet Gill, the Labour MP for
OL,17,FBirmingham Edgbaston, went further
OL,18,Fsaying "The intervention denies
OL,19,Fdemocratic scrutiny."
OL,21,F"It's got to balance the books"
